theorem isClosed_and_P3_implies_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP3 : Topology.P3 (X := X) A) :
    IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  -- From `P3` and the fact that `A` is closed we get `A ⊆ interior A`.
  have h₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
    simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using hP3
  -- The interior is always contained in the original set.
  have h₂ : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ A := interior_subset
  -- Hence `interior A = A`.
  have h_eq : interior A = A := le_antisymm h₂ h₁
  -- The interior is open, so `A` is open as well.
  simpa [h_eq] using isOpen_interior

theorem P1_iff_P2_of_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) A ↔ Topology.P2 (X := X) A := by
  constructor
  · intro _hP1
    exact Topology.isOpen_implies_P2 (X := X) (A := A) hA
  · intro hP2
    exact Topology.P2_implies_P1 (X := X) (A := A) hP2
